{"title_page": "For\u00eat ancienne de la Rivi\u00e8re-Ch\u00e9zine", "text_new": "{{Infobox protected area\n| name = For\u00eat ancienne de la Rivi\u00e8re-Ch\u00e9zine\n| alt_name = \n| iucn_category = III\n| iucn_ref =\n| photo = \n| photo_width = \n| photo_alt = \n| photo_caption = \n| map = Quebec\n| map_width = \n| map_alt = \n| map_caption = \n| relief = yes\n| label =\n| label_position =\n| mark =\n| marker_size =\n| location = [[Lac-Walker, Quebec|Lac-Walker]], C\u00f4te-Nord, Quebec, Canada\n| nearest_city = \n| coordinates = {{coord|50.269220|-67.318555|display=it}}\n| coords_ref = \n| area_ha = \n| designation =\n| authorized =\n| created =\n| designated =\n| established = 2005\n| visitation_num = \n| visitation_year = \n| visitation_ref =\n| governing_body = \n| administrator = [[Ministry of Energy and Natural Resources (Quebec)|Ministry of Energy and Natural Resources]]\n| operator =\n| owner =\n| world_heritage_site =\n}}\nThe '''Rivi\u00e8re-Ch\u00e9zine old forest''' is an [[exceptional forest ecosystem]] located in [[Saint-Gabriel-de-Valcartier]] ([[Quebec]]). It protects a [[yellow birch]] to [[balsam fir|fir]] who is over {{convert|160|years}}. It is located in [[zec Batiscan-Neilson]].\n\n== Toponymy ==\nThe Rivi\u00e8re-Ch\u00e9zine old forest takes its name from the [[Ch\u00e9zine River (Sainte-Anne River)]], which borders it on the northeast side. The name of the watercourse, of unknown origin, was noted in 1945.<ref name=CTQ>{{cite web|url=http://www.toponymie.gouv.qc.ca/ct/ToposWeb/fiche.aspx?no_seq=398788|title=Rivi\u00e8re-Ch\u00e9zine old forest|series=Bank of place names from Quebec|web site=Commission de toponymie |access-date=February 2, 2020}}.</ref>\n\n== Geography ==\nThe Rivi\u00e8re-Ch\u00e9zine Old Forest is located {{convert|50|km}} northwest of [[Quebec (city)|Quebec]], in the municipality of [[Saint-Gabriel-de-Valcartier]].<ref name=CTQ/> It has an area of {{convert|49|ha}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.environnement.gouv.qc.ca/biodiversite/aires_protegees/registre/reg-design/ForetAncienne.pdf|title=Exceptional forest ecosystem: Old growth forest|series=Register of protected areas in Quebec|author=Ministry of the Environment and the Fight against Climate Change|year=2009|page=14|access-date=February 2, 2020 }}.</ref>. The forest is located in a mountainous region interspersed with deep valleys with steep slopes. The forest itself is located on an escarpment exposed to the east with medium to steep slopes. The soil, usually [[tillite|till]] is deep, well-drained soil. The forest is bordered to the northeast by the Ch\u00e9zine river.<ref name=\"MRNF_p1\">{{harvsp|Ministry of Natural Resources and Wildlife|2007|p=1}}.</ref>\n\nThe forest is located in [[zec Batiscan-Neilson]].\n\n== Flora ==\nThe old forest of Rivi\u00e8re-Ch\u00e9zine is a forest mainly dominated by the [[yellow birch]] (''Betula alleghaniensis''). Since it is a species susceptible to water stress, oblique drainage probably favored its growth. The average age of the trees is around {{convert|160|years}}, but the dominant trees are over {{convert|185|years}} and something like {{convert|60|cm} } of diameter. A yellow birch even exceeds {{convert|300|years}} and has a trunk of {{convert|92|cm}} in diameter. The forest also has many characteristics of old growth forest, such as an irregular structure, woody debris on the ground, [[chicot]] s and trees with imposing diameters.<ref name=\"MRNF_p1\"/>\n\nThe shrub layer, we especially observe the [[maple with ears of corn]] (''Acer spicatum ''), which is accompanied by the [[viburnum antlers]] (''Viburnum lantanoides'') [[elderberry]] (''Sambucus racemosa''), [[Balsam fir]] (''Abies balsamea'') and [[gadellier lacustre]] (''Ribes lacustre''). The herbaceous layer is occupied by ferns of the genus ''[[Dryopteris]]'' sp., The [[beech beetle]] (''Phegopteris connectilis''), the [[mountain oxalid]] (''Oxalis montana'') and [[pubescent bramble]] (''Rubus pubescens'').<ref name=\"MRNF_p1\"/>\n\n== Notes and references ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== Appendices ==\n=== Related articles ===\n* [[Ch\u00e9zine River]]\n* [[Zec Batiscan-Neilson]]\n\n=== External links ===\n\n=== Bibliography ===\n*{{Book|auteur1=Ministry of Natural Resources and Wildlife|title=For\u00eat For\u00eat de la Rivi\u00e8re-Ch\u00e9zine|year=2007|url=https://mffp.gouv.qc.ca/publications/forets/knowledge/ecosystems-chezine.pdf}}.\n\n{{Portal|nature conservation|Capitale-Nationale|wood and forest}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rivi\u00e8re-Ch\u00e9zine, ancient forest}}\n[[Category:Exceptional forest ecosystem of Quebec]]\n[[Category:Protected areas of Capitale-Nationale]]\n[[Category:Protected areas established in 2007]]\n[[Category:La Jacques-Cartier Regional County Municipality]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox protected area\n| name = For\u00eat ancienne de la Rivi\u00e8re-Ch\u00e9zine\n| alt_name = \n| iucn_category = III\n| iucn_ref =\n| photo = \n| photo_width = \n| photo_alt = \n| photo_caption = \n| map = Quebec\n| map_width = \n| map_alt = \n| map_caption = \n| relief = yes\n| label =\n| label_position =\n| mark =\n| marker_size =\n| location = [[Lac-Walker, Quebec|Lac-Walker]], C\u00f4te-Nord, Quebec, Canada\n| nearest_city = \n| coordinates = {{coord|50.269220|-67.318555|display=it}}\n| coords_ref = \n| area_ha = \n| designation =\n| authorized =\n| created =\n| designated =\n| established = 2005\n| visitation_num = \n| visitation_year = \n| visitation_ref =\n| governing_body = \n| administrator = [[Ministry of Energy and Natural Resources (Quebec)|Ministry of Energy and Natural Resources]]\n| operator =\n| owner =\n| world_heritage_site =\n}}\nThe '''Rivi\u00e8re-Ch\u00e9zine old forest''' is an [[exceptional forest ecosystem]] located in [[Saint-Gabriel-de-Valcartier]] ([[Quebec]]). It protects a [[yellow birch]] to [[balsam fir|fir]] who is over {{convert|160|years}}. It is located in [[zec Batiscan-Neilson]].\n\n== Toponymy ==\nThe Rivi\u00e8re-Ch\u00e9zine old forest takes its name from the [[Ch\u00e9zine River (Sainte-Anne River)]], which borders it on the northeast side. The name of the watercourse, of unknown origin, was noted in 1945.<ref name=CTQ>{{cite web|url=http://www.toponymie.gouv.qc.ca/ct/ToposWeb/fiche.aspx?no_seq=398788|title=Rivi\u00e8re-Ch\u00e9zine old forest|series=Bank of place names from Quebec|web site=Commission de toponymie |access-date=February 2, 2020}}.</ref>\n\n== Geography ==\nThe Rivi\u00e8re-Ch\u00e9zine Old Forest is located {{convert|50|km}} northwest of [[Quebec (city)|Quebec]], in the municipality of [[Saint-Gabriel-de-Valcartier]].<ref name=CTQ/> It has an area of {{convert|49|ha}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.environnement.gouv.qc.ca/biodiversite/aires_protegees/registre/reg-design/ForetAncienne.pdf|title=Exceptional forest ecosystem: Old growth forest|series=Register of protected areas in Quebec|author=Ministry of the Environment and the Fight against Climate Change|year=2009|page=14|access-date=February 2, 2020 }}.</ref>. The forest is located in a mountainous region interspersed with deep valleys with steep slopes. The forest itself is located on an escarpment exposed to the east with medium to steep slopes. The soil, usually [[tillite|till]] is deep, well-drained soil. The forest is bordered to the northeast by the Ch\u00e9zine river.<ref name=\"MRNF_p1\">{{harvsp|Ministry of Natural Resources and Wildlife|2007|p=1}}.</ref>\n\nThe forest is located in [[zec Batiscan-Neilson]].\n\n== Flora ==\nThe old forest of Rivi\u00e8re-Ch\u00e9zine is a forest mainly dominated by the [[yellow birch]] (''Betula alleghaniensis''). Since it is a species susceptible to water stress, oblique drainage probably favored its growth. The average age of the trees is around {{convert|160|years}}, but the dominant trees are over {{convert|185|years}} and something like {{convert|60|cm} } of diameter. A yellow birch even exceeds {{convert|300|years}} and has a trunk of {{convert|92|cm}} in diameter. The forest also has many characteristics of old growth forest, such as an irregular structure, woody debris on the ground, [[chicot]] s and trees with imposing diameters.<ref name=\"MRNF_p1\"/>\n\nThe shrub layer, we especially observe the [[maple with ears of corn]] (''Acer spicatum ''), which is accompanied by the [[viburnum antlers]] (''Viburnum lantanoides'') [[elderberry]] (''Sambucus racemosa''), [[Balsam fir]] (''Abies balsamea'') and [[gadellier lacustre]] (''Ribes lacustre''). The herbaceous layer is occupied by ferns of the genus ''[[Dryopteris]]'' sp., The [[beech beetle]] (''Phegopteris connectilis''), the [[mountain oxalid]] (''Oxalis montana'') and [[pubescent bramble]] (''Rubus pubescens'').<ref name=\"MRNF_p1\"/>\n\n== Notes and references ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== Appendices ==\n=== Related articles ===\n* [[Ch\u00e9zine River]]\n* [[Zec Batiscan-Neilson]]\n\n=== External links ===\n\n=== Bibliography ===\n*{{Book|auteur1=Ministry of Natural Resources and Wildlife|title=For\u00eat For\u00eat de la Rivi\u00e8re-Ch\u00e9zine|year=2007|url=https://mffp.gouv.qc.ca/publications/forets/knowledge/ecosystems-chezine.pdf}}.\n\n{{Portal|nature conservation|Capitale-Nationale|wood and forest}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rivi\u00e8re-Ch\u00e9zine, ancient forest}}\n[[Category:Exceptional forest ecosystem of Quebec]]\n[[Category:Protected area in the Capitale-Nationale]]\n[[Category:Protected area created in 2007]]\n[[Category:La Jacques-Cartier]]\n", "name_user": "Veillg1", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eAppendices", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/For%C3%AAt_ancienne_de_la_Rivi%C3%A8re-Ch%C3%A9zine"}
