 the top five riders and constructors after round sixteen has concluded.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://resources.motogp.com/files/results/2014/AUS/MotoGP/RAC/worldstanding.pdf?v3_95249eae|title=Standings |date=2014|website=resources.motogp.com |format=PDF|access-date=2019-08-26}}</ref>\n\n{{col-start}}\n{{col-2}}\n;Riders' Championship standings\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 95%;\"\n|-\n! {{Tooltip|Pos.|Position}}\n! Rider\n! Points\n|-\n|align=center| 1\n| {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Marc M\u00e1rquez]]\n|align=right| 312\n|-\n|align=center| 2\n| {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Valentino Rossi]]\n|align=right| 255\n|-\n|align=center| 3\n| {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Dani Pedrosa]]\n|align=right| 247\n|-\n|align=center| 4\n| {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Jorge Lorenzo]]\n|align=right| 230\n|-\n|align=center| 5\n| {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Andrea Dovizioso]]\n|align=right| 166\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n;Constructors' Championship standings\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 95%;\"\n|-\n! {{Tooltip|Pos.|Position}}\n! Constructor\n! Points\n|-\n|align=center| 1\n| {{flagicon|JPN}} [[Honda]]\n|align=right| 359\n|-\n|align=center| 2\n| {{flagicon|JPN}} [[Yamaha Motor Company|Yamaha]]\n|align=right| 314\n|-\n|align=center| 3\n| {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Ducati]]\n|align=right| 189\n|-\n|align=center| 4\n| {{flagicon|CHE}} [[Forward Racing|Forward Yamaha]]\n|align=right| 129\n|-\n|align=center| 5\n| {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Aprilia|ART]]\n|align=right| 13\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n* <small>'''Note''': Only the top five positions are included for both sets of standings.</small>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{MotoGP_race_report\n| Name_of_race = [[Australian motorcycle Grand Prix]]\n| Year_of_race = 2014\n| Previous_race_in_season = [[2014 Japanese motorcycle Grand Prix|2014 Japanese Grand Prix]]\n| Next_race_in_season = [[2014 Malaysian motorcycle Grand Prix|2014 Malaysian Grand Prix]]\n| Previous_year's_race = [[2013 Australian motorcycle Grand Prix|2013 Australian Grand Prix]]\n| Next_year's_race = [[2015 Australian motorcycle Grand Prix|2015 Australian Grand Prix]]\n}}\n\n[[Category:2014 MotoGP race reports]]\n[[Category:2014 in Australian motorsport|Motorcycle Grand Prix]]\n[[Category:Australian motorcycle Grand Prix]]\n[[Category:Motorsport at Phillip Island]]\n[[Category:October 2014 sports events in Australia|Australian motorcycle Grand Prix]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Grand Prix motorcycle race report\n| Grand Prix = Australian\n| flag = Australia\n| Official_Name = [[Tissot]] Australian Motorcycle Grand Prix<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/database/races/2014-australian-motogp|title=2014 Australian MotoGP|date=13 June 2014|website=Motorsportmagazine.com|accessdate=24 May 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.progcovers.com/motor/motogp2014.html|title=Magazine Programme Covers|website=Progcovers.com|accessdate=3 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.progcovers.com/motor/phillipisland.html|title=Phillip Island Circuit - The Motor Racing Programme Covers Project|first=Malcolm|last=Mitchell|website=Progcovers.com|accessdate=24 May 2018}}</ref>\n| Location =[[Phillip Island Grand Prix Circuit]]\n| Image = Phillip Island Grand Prix Circuit.svg\n| Course_mi = 2.763\n| Course_km = 4.448\n| Race_No = 16\n| Season_No = 18\n| Date = 19 October\n| Year = 2014\n|Pole_Rider_MotoGP          = [[Marc M\u00e1rquez]]\n|Pole_Rider_MotoGP_Country  = Spain\n|Pole_Rider_MotoGP_Bike     = [[Honda]]\n|Pole_Time_MotoGP           = 1:28.408\n|Fast_Rider_MotoGP          = [[Valentino Rossi]]\n|Fast_Rider_MotoGP_Country  = Italy\n|Fast_Rider_MotoGP_Bike     = [[Yamaha Motor Company|Yamaha]]\n|Fast_Time_MotoGP           = 1:29.605 on lap 9\n|First_Rider_MotoGP         = [[Valentino Rossi]]\n|First_Rider_MotoGP_Country = Italy\n|First_Rider_MotoGP_Bike    = [[Yamaha Motor Company|Yamaha]]\n|Second_Rider_MotoGP        = [[Jorge Lorenzo]]\n|Second_Rider_MotoGP_Country= Spain\n|Second_Rider_MotoGP_Bike   = [[Yamaha Motor Company|Yamaha]]\n|Third_Rider_MotoGP         = [[Bradley Smith (motorcyclist)|Bradley Smith]]\n|Third_Rider_MotoGP_Country = United Kingdom\n|Third_Rider_MotoGP_Bike    = [[Yamaha Motor Company|Yamaha]]\n|Pole_Rider_Moto2           = [[Esteve Rabat]]\n|Pole_Rider_Moto2_Country   = Spain\n|Pole_Rider_Moto2_Bike      = [[Kalex]]\n|Pole_Time_Moto2            = 1:32.470\n|Fast_Rider_Moto2           = [[Maverick Vi\u00f1ales]]\n|Fast_Rider_Moto2_Country   = Spain\n|Fast_Rider_Moto2_Bike      = [[Kalex]]\n|Fast_Time_Moto2            = 1:33.066 on lap 25\n|First_Rider_Moto2          = [[Maverick Vi\u00f1ales]]\n|First_Rider_Moto2_Country  = Spain\n|First_Rider_Moto2_Bike     = [[Kalex]]\n|Second_Rider_Moto2         = [[Thomas L\u00fcthi]]\n|Second_Rider_Moto2_Country = Switzerland\n|Second_Rider_Moto2_Bike    = [[Eskil Suter|Suter]]\n|Third_Rider_Moto2          = [[Esteve Rabat]]\n|Third_Rider_Moto2_Country  = Spain\n|Third_Rider_Moto2_Bike     = [[Kalex]]\n|Pole_Rider_Moto3           = [[\u00c1lex M\u00e1rquez]]\n|Pole_Rider_Moto3_Country   = Spain\n|Pole_Rider_Moto3_Bike      = [[Honda]]\n|Pole_Time_Moto3            = 1:36.050\n|Fast_Rider_Moto3           = [[Jack Miller (motorcyclist)|Jack Miller]]\n|Fast_Rider_Moto3_Country   = Australia\n|Fast_Rider_Moto3_Bike      = [[KTM]]\n|Fast_Time_Moto3            = 1:36.302 on lap 3\n|First_Rider_Moto3          = [[Jack Miller (motorcyclist)|Jack Miller]]\n|First_Rider_Moto3_Country  = Australia\n|First_Rider_Moto3_Bike     = [[KTM]]\n|Second_Rider_Moto3         = [[\u00c1lex M\u00e1rquez]]\n|Second_Rider_Moto3_Country = Spain\n|Second_Rider_Moto3_Bike    = [[Honda]]\n|Third_Rider_Moto3          = [[\u00c1lex Rins]]\n|Third_Rider_Moto3_Country  = Spain\n|Third_Rider_Moto3_Bike     = [[Honda]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2014 Australian motorcycle Grand Prix''' was the sixteenth round of the [[2014 Grand Prix motorcycle racing season]]. It was held at the [[Phillip Island Grand Prix Circuit]] in [[Phillip Island (Victoria)|Phillip Island]] on 19 October 2014.\n\nIn his 250th premier class start, [[Valentino Rossi]] took his second victory of the season, after benefitting from an accident for [[Marc M\u00e1rquez]], while he was leading the race. It was Rossi's sixth win at the circuit, after five successive wins from [[2001 Grand Prix motorcycle racing season|2001]] to [[2005 Grand Prix motorcycle racing season|2005]]. Second place went to Rossi's teammate [[Jorge Lorenzo]] finished in second place, while [[Tech 3]]'s [[Bradley Smith (motorcyclist)|Bradley Smith]] finished in third place, recording his first premier class podium, after [[Ducati]]'s [[Cal Crutchlow]] crashed out late on. As a result, it was the first all-[[Yamaha Motor Company|Yamaha]] podium since the [[2008 French motorcycle Grand Prix|2008 French Grand Prix]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/motorsport/29679710|title=Valentino Rossi wins as Marc Marquez exits|work=[[BBC Sport]]|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=19 October 2014|accessdate=27 December 2014}}</ref> and the first time since the [[2011 Australian motorcycle Grand Prix|2011 Australian Grand Prix]] where all three riders on the podium were of the same manufacturer. For the first time since the [[2009 Dutch TT]], both [[Repsol Honda]] riders failed to finish the race; further to M\u00e1rquez's accident, [[Dani Pedrosa]] collided with [[Andrea Iannone]], causing both riders to retire from the race.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.speedweek.com/motogp/news/65366/Phillip-Island-Schwarzer-Sonntag-fuer-Honda.html|title=Schwarzer Sonntag f\u00fcr Honda|language=German|trans-title=Black Sunday for Honda|date=20 October 2014|accessdate=30 December 2014|first=G\u00fcnther|last=Wiesinger|work=Speedweek|publisher=Red Bulletin Schweiz AG}}</ref> [[Karel Abraham]], [[Stefan Bradl]] and [[Pol Espargar\u00f3]] also crashed out of the race, and only 14 of the 23 starters reached the finish.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.motogp.com/en/news/2014/MotoGP+Australia+Race+Rossi|title=Rossi takes 82nd premier class victory in incident packed race|work=MotoGP.com|publisher=[[Dorna Sports]]|date=19 October 2014|accessdate=30 December 2014}}</ref><ref name=MGPrace>{{cite web|url=http://resources.motogp.com/files/results/2014/AUS/MotoGP/RAC/Classification.pdf|format=[[Portable Document Format|PDF]]|title=Tissot Australian Grand Prix&nbsp;\u2013 MotoGP&nbsp;\u2013 Race classification|work=MotoGP.com|publisher=[[Dorna Sports]]|date=19 October 2014|accessdate=30 December 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn the support categories, [[Maverick Vi\u00f1ales]] took his third win of the season in Moto2, ahead of [[Thomas L\u00fcthi]] and championship leader [[Esteve Rabat]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.motogp.com/en/news/2014/Moto2+Australia+Race+Viales|title=Vi\u00f1ales takes the win in exciting Australian contest|work=MotoGP.com|publisher=[[Dorna Sports]]|date=19 October 2014|accessdate=27 December 2014}}</ref> In Moto3, [[Jack Miller (motorcyclist)|Jack Miller]] took his fifth win of the season on home soil, in a photo finish; he finished just clear of Estrella Galicia 0,0 teammates [[\u00c1lex M\u00e1rquez]] (the championship leader) and [[\u00c1lex Rins]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.motogp.com/en/news/2014/Miller+shows+determination+and+skill+for+classy+win|title=Miller shows determination and skill for classy win|work=MotoGP.com|publisher=[[Dorna Sports]]|date=20 October 2014|accessdate=27 December 2014}}</ref> The top six riders were covered by just under a quarter of a second at the finish.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://resources.motogp.com/files/results/2014/AUS/Moto3/RAC/Classification.pdf|format=[[Portable Document Format|PDF]]|title=Tissot Australian Grand Prix&nbsp;\u2013 Moto3&nbsp;\u2013 Race classification|work=MotoGP.com|publisher=[[Dorna Sports]]|date=19 October 2014|accessdate=27 December 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Classification==\n===MotoGP===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 95%;\"\n! Pos.\n! No.\n! Rider\n! Team\n! Manufacturer\n! Laps\n! Time/Retired\n! Grid\n! Points\n|-\n! 1\n| 46\n| {{flagicon|ITA}} ''